modules.description: Provides functions like `compare`, `equal`, and `hash` that mirror the behavior of pre-4.08 Pervasives, working with basic types such as integers, strings, and tuples. Offers a consistent interface for comparing and hashing values across different OCaml versions. Enables seamless migration of codebases from older OCaml versions by substituting Pervasives with Stdlib equivalents.

The module provides basic data types and operations for integers, floating-point numbers, strings, characters, and lists, along with input/output functions and format string handling. It supports arithmetic operations, special IEEE 754 floating-point values, and formatted I/O with customizable conversion specifications. Examples include performing overflow-safe integer arithmetic, handling infinities and NaNs in floating-point calculations, and using format strings to parse and print structured data. It serves as a foundational library for common programming tasks.
